'''《特纳日记》'''（{{lang-en|''The Turner Diaries''}}）是由安德鲁·麦克唐纳于1978年撰写的政治小说。书中描绘了因美国政府没收私人枪支导致的右翼革命战争，最终[[联邦政府|联邦政府]]被推翻，并且伴随而来的[[种族清洗|种族清洗]]消灭了所有美国犹太人、[[同性恋者|同性恋者]]及非白种人。<ref name="ADL-TD">{{Cite news|url=http://www.adl.org/learn/ext_us/Turner_Diaries.asp|title=Extremism: The Turner Diaries|publisher=[[Anti-Defamation_League|Anti-Defamation League]]|accessdate=2007-07-18|year=2007|archive-date=2007-06-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070630214713/http://www.adl.org/learn/ext_us/Turner_Diaries.asp|dead-url=no}}</ref>

该书真实作者是物理学家[[威廉·皮爾斯|威廉·皮爾斯]]，安德鲁·麦克唐纳是他的笔名。此人创立了[[新纳粹|新纳粹]]组织国家联盟，宣扬白人优越论，排斥非白人和非基督徒<ref name="nyttv">{{Cite news|url=http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9505E4DF1631F930A15753C1A9669C8B63|title=Television Review; The Web as Home for Racism and Hate|last=Salamon|first=Julie|date=2000-10-23|work=The New York Times|publisher=Arthur Ochs Sulzberger, Jr.|accessdate=2007-09-05|archive-date=2009-02-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090217015053/http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9505E4DF1631F930A15753C1A9669C8B63|dead-url=no}}</ref>。自1978年该书出版以来，《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》将其评为“露骨的[[种族主义|种族主义]]和[[反犹主义|反犹主义]]”政治小说；[[南方贫困法律中心|南方贫困法律中心]]称其为“右翼种族主义者的圣经”。<ref>''The New York Times'' [http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=990CE7D7143CF935A15757C0A963958260 April 26, 1995] {{Wayback|url=http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=990CE7D7143CF935A15757C0A963958260 |date=20090220163827 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.splcenter.org/intel/intelreport/article.jsp?aid=490|title=Southern Poverty Law Center|accessdate=2009-10-16|publisher=Splcenter.org|archive-date=2009-10-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091018155229/http://www.splcenter.org/intel/intelreport/article.jsp?aid=490|dead-url=no}}</ref>

作为文艺作品，《特纳日记》虚构了通过发动种族战争从而将美国变成白人[[民族国家|民族国家]]，从而推行白人优越主义和优生学政策。 <ref name="voice1">{{Cite news|url=http://www.villagevoice.com/news/the-nazi-on-the-bestseller-list-6417005|title=The Nazi on the Bestseller List|last=Harkavy|first=Ward|date=2000-11-15|work=[[The_Village_Voice|The Village Voice]]|publisher=|accessdate=2007-09-05|archive-date=2016-03-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328010656/http://www.villagevoice.com/news/the-nazi-on-the-bestseller-list-6417005|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|last=Shinbaum|first=Myrna|title=Q & A on The Turner Diaries|date=1996-05-16|url=http://www.adl.org/presrele/militi_71/2737_71.asp|publisher=Anti-Defamation League}}</ref>

